+CONFIG_KPROBES
+  Kprobes allows you to trap at almost any kernel address, using
+  register_kprobe(), and providing a callback function.  This is useful
+  for kernel debugging, non-intrusive instrumentation and testing.  If
+  in doubt, say "N".
